(firstQuint)Effects of DASH Diet on Corticosteroids Medication Use.

 Objective: To determine the effects of the Dietary Approaches to Stop Hypertension (DASH) diet on the metabolic side effects of corticosteroids medications use.

 Design: A randomized clinical trial was undertaken in 60 patients on corticosteroid therapy for 10 weeks.

 Patients were randomly assigned to a DASH or control diet.

 Fasting blood sample were measured to determine blood glucose and lipid profile.

 Blood pressure and anthropometric measurements were measured based on the standard guidelines.

